The paper deals with deep neural networks and their properties related to depth, which are typically studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities (cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for image classification tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper introduces a sample compression representation of neural networks, which is a technique used in data compression and computational complexity theory (cs.DS).
